# Brief: Q2 Security Posture Findings

This report summarizes findings from our Q1-Q2 2026 security posture assessment
of Acme's production infrastructure. The assessment was commissioned to fulfill
deliverable §4.2 of the master engagement contract.

## What we assessed

- Public-facing services: web tier, API gateway, CDN configuration
- IAM posture: role definitions, least-privilege audit, service account lifecycle
- Secrets management: rotation policies, deployment-time injection patterns
- Logging and audit trail: SIEM coverage gaps, retention policy compliance

## What we did not assess

- Endpoint security (employee laptops) — out of scope per engagement contract
- Application-layer vulnerabilities — separate engagement (#ACME-2026-Q3-APPSEC)
- Physical security — out of scope

## Method

Reviewed configuration exports from production AWS account, conducted 6 interviews
with Acme platform and security engineers, ran the standard CIS benchmarks against
configuration snapshots from 2026-03-01 and 2026-05-01.

## Known sensitivities

- Acme is mid-acquisition; one finding (IAM #3) intersects with the diligence
  process and should be flagged for separate handling in the receipt cover.
- A prior interim report (`interim.2`, delivered 2026-05-01) discussed an early
  version of IAM finding #3 — ensure consistency or explicitly note the change.

